Press Releases.Title: 1 New Case of Locally Transmitted Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 11 July 2021, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed 1 new case of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection, who is currently unlinked.

2.   There are 7 imported cases, who have already been placed on Stay-Home Notice (SHN) or isolated upon arrival in Singapore. 1 was detected upon arrival in Singapore, while 6 developed the illness during SHN or isolation.

3.   In total, there are 8 new cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore today.

4.   We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.

 

 

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
11 JULY 2021
